-- Futures rise on bank rescue plan
-- 
-- Sun Oct 12, 2008 7:31pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/10/12/us-markets-stocks-idUSTRE49B3PW20081012

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Stock futures rose on Sunday evening as central bankers and government leaders took steps to solve the financial crisis that has been crippling global markets. 

 S&P 500 futures rose 29.8 points. Dow Jones industrial average futures rose 252 points, and Nasdaq 100 futures climbed 31.25 points. (Reporting by  Vivianne Rodrigues  and  Walter Brandimarte ; Editing by  Andrea Ricci )